    {
      "name": "Biomet Consultants — Clinical Trials & CDM",
      "company_profile": "Biomet Consultants: Clinical data management consulting firm led by a Data Management Leader with 20+ years of experience in Pharmaceutical and CRO sectors. Principal consultant held Associate Director-level CDM roles at Taiho Oncology (2020–present), Celgene Corporation (2017–2019), and Roche Pharmaceuticals (2010–2017), plus earlier CDM and pharmacovigilance roles at Integrium, Cmed Group, and Pfizer. Therapeutic areas: Oncology, Hematology, Rare Disease, Cardiovascular, Metabolic, Neuroscience, Virology, and Medical Devices. Clinical trial phases I, II, and III. Technical skills: Medidata Rave, ClinPlus Data Management (paper and eDC), Microsoft Power BI, Tibco Spotfire, Timeaus, Microsoft Project. Core capabilities: CRO oversight and vendor governance, eCRF/CRF design and development, database build through database lock, CDISC standards (CDASH, SDTM, ADaM), integrated data review plans (IDRPs), ICH GCP compliance, SAE reconciliation, medical coding (MedDRA, WHODrug), pharmacovigilance and safety reporting (Argus Safety), SOP development, regulatory submission support (IND/NDA/BLA), data transfer agreements, KPI tracking, and inspection readiness. Experienced managing outsourced clinical programs with global CRO partners. Rutgers Mini-MBA BioPharma Innovation Certificate. Located in New Jersey. Seeking clinical data management services, CRO data management support, data quality and cleaning services, and CDM consulting contracts — both as prime and as subcontractor under established primes (Leidos Biomedical, Westat, ICF, Emmes, Rho, Theradex).",
